The paper also discusses the complexity class PPAD, which is a class of problems related to the computation of fixed points and equilibria, and is often studied in the context of computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper uses graph theory and algorithms to construct a reduction, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the reduction in market equilibrium, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
